# EXPERIMENT 4\par
\par
## TITLE\par
\par
Kubernetes Deployment of RoadSense AI\par
\par
## AIM\par
\par
To deploy the RoadSense AI backend as a Kubernetes application with sidecar containers and expose it through a service.\par
\par
## SOFTWARE USED\par
\par
- Kubernetes\par
- Minikube or Docker Desktop Kubernetes\par
- kubectl\par
- YAML deployment file\par
\par
## DEPLOYMENT FILE\par
\par
The Kubernetes configuration is stored in `deployment.yaml`. It defines:\par
\par
- RoadSense backend container\par
- Redis sidecar container\par
- BusyBox sidecar container\par
- Three replicas\par
- NodePort service\par
- Optional OpenAI API key through Kubernetes Secret\par
\par
## PROCEDURE\par
\par
1. Kubernetes was enabled using Minikube or Docker Desktop.\par
2. The deployment file `deployment.yaml` was created.\par
3. The backend container image was referenced in the deployment manifest.\par
4. Redis and BusyBox sidecars were added to demonstrate multi-container pod deployment.\par
5. The deployment was applied using `kubectl apply`.\par
6. Running pods were checked using `kubectl get pods`.\par
7. The service was verified using `kubectl get services`.\par
\par
## COMMANDS USED\par
\par
```bash\par
kubectl apply -f deployment.yaml\par
kubectl get pods\par
kubectl get deployments\par
kubectl get services\par
kubectl describe deployment roadsense-deployment\par
```\par
